**Issue**: #739 - Main CI red: Deploy to staging
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Every deploy is blocked — no staging or production deploys can go through |
| Complexity | LOW | Single credential rotation, zero code changes required |
| Confidence | HIGH | CI log shows literal "Not Authorized" from Railway API, exact fix is documented |

### Root Cause

The `RAILWAY_TOKEN` GitHub secret has expired or been revoked. Railway's GraphQL API returns `"Not Authorized"` when the pre-flight validation step calls `{me{id}}`. The token validation was added in `3dfb995` on the same day as this failure — it surfaced a pre-existing bad credential.

### Fix (no code changes)

1. Go to `https://railway.com/account/tokens` — create a **permanent** token named `github-actions`
2. `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN --repo alexsiri7/reli`
3. `gh run rerun 25007185051 --repo alexsiri7/reli`

One rotation unblocks both staging and production (they share the same `RAILWAY_TOKEN`).

